name: The Ultimate 2023 Burning Van
seller_notes: QR Code Link to This Post Calling all free spirits, Burning Man enthusiasts, and seekers of unforgettable experiences! Elevate your Burning Man journey with a van that's tailor-made for the Playa and beyond. Introducing an exceptional van that's been thoughtfully upgraded and crafted to make your Burning Man 2023 truly extraordinary. Everybody, meet Giraldo: the ultimate 2023 Burning Van Standout Features for Your Burner Adventure: Reliable Upgrades: Get ready for an epic adventure with peace of mind. We've recently replaced the alternator and turbo resonator to ensure smooth performance as you embark on your Burning Man odyssey. Camper Oasis: Embrace comfort in the heart of the desert with an interior that's 90% finished as a camper. Revel in the convenience of a refrigerator, sink, and 30-gallon water tank. While the sink's finishing touches are just a water pump replacement away (around $100 and easy to do), the stage is set for you to create the perfect setup. Solar Power: This van is equipped with a full solar system that offers true off-grid liberation. With 4 panels producing a whopping 780 watts and two 12-volt deep cell sealed batteries connected in a 24-volt system, you'll have all the energy you need. The 5000-watt inverter ensures you're powered up for all your Burning Man adventures. Versatile Interior Space: Created for both practicality and comfort, this van boasts ample storage and counter space. Its layout is designed to accommodate a queen-size bed, and we're including a full-size foam mattress for your convenience. Stealthy Camping: The desert is your playground, and this van is your secret weapon. Its inconspicuous appearance, blacked-out windows, and discreet design allow you to camp anywhere, undetected.  Proven Performance: With a well-maintained, battle-tested 5-cylinder Mercedes Benz engine, this van is built to handle the desert's demands and beyond, known to reach over a million miles of epic journeys. Staggering Storage Capacity: I recently moved out of my apartment and was able to fit everything I own in the underbelly. You will not run out of room.  Nomadic Soul: Range anxiety does not exist when you ride with Giraldo: I was able to cross half of Nevada on half a tank of diesel. While he might not go fast - he can't run quite as quickly as he used to - but he will go far. He's made multiple trips across the country - are you ready to add your chapters to the story?  Like any sprinter van that's been around the block a couple of times, Giraldo has some personality quirks. He needs to be locked manually and you have to access storage from the outside. The interior is also 6 feet high, so I also can't fully stand up inside, which is the primary reason why I'm looking to sell. He also requires some attention - a Maxx fan, rewiring the electrical, replacing the pump on the sink, treating rust on the body - that I can't provide right now. If you want to put your handiness to the test, Giraldo is a perfect opportunity to practice.  The Playa is waiting, and this van is your ticket to a one-of-a-kind Burning Man 2023. Whether it's your first burn or you're a seasoned desert wanderer, this van promises to be the epicenter of your unforgettable journey. Reach out now to secure your chance to own this incredible adventure vehicle. Let the anticipation build – your Burning Man adventure begins with the ignition of this remarkable van. Price: This baby is insured at $14,000 and the solar plus electrical add on an additional 6k. But I'm flexy on price and prepared to throw in amenities to make your future adventures that much smoother - make me an offer!

Source: Edmunds * The Lexus IS line showcases a bold and captivating design, with additional interior room, and better handling than before. In front there is an incredibly stylish yet aggressive spindle grille and angled headlights. The rest of the body is exquisitely shaped, with dramatic, aerodynamic lines. Plus, with its wider stance, stretched wheelbase, and underbody panels to further reduce wind resistance, this car was designed to move. Lexus gives you a wide range of model variations to pick from. There is the 204hp IS 250 and IS 250 F Sport, as well as the 306hp IS 350 and IS 350 F Sport. Each can be purchased with Rear-Wheel Drive or All-Wheel Drive. The IS 250 models come with a 2.5L V6, that gets up to 21 MPG City and 30 MPG hwy. The IS 350 Models come with a 3.5L V6 that gets up to 19 MPG City and 28 MPG hwy. The IS interior is incredible. It has low sport seating in front, and close to 3 extra inches of legroom in back. The highly comfortable NuLuxe faux-leather seats are not to be missed, and extra headroom in front and back will keep you from feeling constrained. Plus, if you purchase any of the F Sport models, prepare to be amazed by the advanced digital instrument cluster. Lexus has given the IS line a generous array of standard features. Some items include a power moonroof, push-button start, drive mode select and an 8-speaker Sound System that comes with a 7-inch color screen. Some standard safety features you get are 10 airbags, anti-lock brakes, brake assist, and traction control. As an option, some incredible safety technology available includes the Pre-Collision System with Dynamic Radar Cruise Control, Intuitive Parking Assist, and Blind Spot Monitor with Rear Cross-Traffic Alert. name: 2000 BMW 528i
seller_notes: QR Code Link to This Post 2000 BMW 528i SedanExterior Color: Aspen Silver MetallicInterior Color: BlackVIN: WBADM634XYGU18573Stock Number: 42193R1License Plate: 4KXP408Mileage: 150,872Engine: 2L NA I6 double overhead cam (DOHC) 24VFuel: GasolineTransmission: AutomaticDrivetrain: Rear Wheel DriveTitle: ClearKey Features:Automatic Climate ControlAirbagsKeyless Entry SystemVehicle overviewBMWs are famous for the suppleness of their ride and the responsiveness of their steering; "firmness without harshness" is the phrase most often bandied about our offices when discussing these cars' uncanny ability to stay connected to the road while communicating almost telepathically with the driver. The 5 Series is no exception. Available in two flavors, 528i or 540i, drivers can choose a sedan or a sport-wagon body style.528i models are powered by a 2.8-liter inline 6-cylinder engine that provides excellent midrange torque and makes 193 horsepower. The 528i comes with a standard five-speed manual transmission, or can be optioned with a five-speed Steptronic automanual transmission.Under the hoods of the 540i sedans and sport wagons sit 4.4-liter, 32-valve V8s that offer zero-to-60 times in the low sixes, make 282 horsepower and can also be mated to five-speed Steptronic automanual transmissions, if desired. The 540i sedan continues to be available with a six-speed manual transmission. If you love to drive, opt for this model and prepare yourself for an invigorating ride. The suspension is pleasantly firm on this lively model, but it is difficult to operate the transmission smoothly.As one would expect in a top-end, luxury/sport vehicle, equipment levels are first rate. Standard fare includes rear self-leveling suspension, car and key programmable memory, dual zone air conditioning and cruise control with steering wheel controls. All-Season Traction (AST), Dynamic Stability Control (DSC) and Dynamic Brake Control are standard on all 2000 5-Series cars. Rain-sensing windshield wipers and Xenon headlights are standard on 540 models and optional on the 528s this year.Standard safety equipment includes 9-mph bumpers, dual airbags, door-mounted side-impact airbags, and a front head-protection system. Three-point seatbelts at all seating positions, impact sensors that unlock the doors and activate the hazard lights in the event of a serious accident, remote keyless entry, two-step unlocking, coded drive-away protection, and a vehicle security system are also standard. Rear-passenger side-impact airbags are optional.Contact Info:The Car StoreButch Washington - (408) 297-97001271 S. First St.San Jose, CA 95110

name: 2009 Chevrolet Suburban LTZ
seller_notes: QR Code Link to This Post 2009 Chevrolet Suburban LTZ We are the 2nd owners and have had this awesome metallic blue 'burban aka "Air Force One" in our family for almost 10 years. It has very light usage with a total of 127,500 current miles = roughly 9,100/year over the 14-year lifespan. It has only been in 4wd a handful of times and was used 99.9% of the time to shuttle our kids around town and for Costco trips. It has never towed a trailer, the hitch was only used for a bike rack. We have always serviced it locally and on time. We installed slightly oversized BF Goodrich (BFG) LT275/60/R20 All-Terrain K02's about 15k miles ago, so those still have a ton of life still in them. This thing purrs and has many many years of great service ahead of it. We are only selling because one son drives himself to HS now, and we have downsized our vehicles. Turn it into a Luxurious Overlander!  Light Grey / Creme leather interior with Walnut trim. 2nd row Captain's chairs, and the usual 3rd-row bench (sits 7). WeatherTech mats in all locations (front wells, 2nd row, middle alley, 3rd row, rear cargo area). All 4 TPMS sensors (tire pressure monitoring system) valve stems were replaced in June. Passed SMOG on 6/30 and is ready to sell. A brand new CARFAX dated 5/20 can be emailed to you upon request. Registration is paid through October and ready for your Overlanding adventures this summer. We are located in Danville. Please email us with any questions. Thanks, Eric

name: 1996 Acura RL, Premium- Low Miles- Original Owners !!!
seller_notes: QR Code Link to This Post Hi Craigslist, We are seeking a New responsible Owner/Owners. That is going to appreciate and take care of The Acura. The way that we have over the years. The Acura is a 1996 Acura RL 4 door sedan, Premium Model, Automatic Transmission V6 3.5 liter engine with 147,000 original miles. We are the original owners. We purchased it at our local Bay Area Acura dealership. Has a retirement gift for me and my wife. It was our 1st brand new car ever. It was our dream car to own and we just loved all the luxury upgrades and the dependability along with having an affordable maintenance car. With out paying the premium prices for maintenance like those high end brands. It was one of the best decisions we have ever made. It is and truly has always been a super super reliable car. That has never let me down through out the years. It runs and drives amazing. It has always been religiously maintained and serviced on time every time. According to age not just the mileage. Since we was both retired we did drive much. Most of the mileage is from going to visit or grandchildren and children in Arizona and Southern California during those days. But know it just been our daily driver. To run errands, doctor appointments, and grocery shopping. It has always been maintenance and serviced by the Acura’s manufacturer maintenance log book and all of the services and maintenance’s are all Up-to-date along with all the maintenance records available. Here is just a brief summary of the most recent maintenance and service reports- New belts/hoses, oils/fluids, pumps, flush’s, sensors, brakes, tuneup, tires, cvc, battery, Ac, and all that good stuff. That the dealership recommended to have done ✅ or that was due ✅ at the 140K /145K maintenance. That equivalent like if it was having the 200K maintenance. In order to keep it continuing, keeping its clean bill of health, and staying up to par. According to Acura’s standards and good stamp of approval !!! The interior is In really good condition. It is fully loaded and has power everything. Lots of premium upgrades and has real leather seats and all the high quality components and upgrades. That Acura had to offer back then. In the premium model. Also everything is good originally working condition. The exterior is in pretty good shape also. Except for the paint fade spots . And The clear coat has been peeling here and there. On the hood, Roof and trunk. But other than that it’s never been in any accident, it’s a non smoking vehicle and no pets. But you can see what I am trying to explain in the pictures my daughter has taken for me . Just for this Ad/posting. So please zoom in the photos. Just for there is no surprise’s. Because the rest of the car paint and body is in good shape for it age. I guess it just has happened over the years from being parked outside in the City in the Sunset district. A lot of our neighbors had the same problem with their vehicles. But that when we lived in the city. We moved out of the city about 10 years ago. Thank goodness 😅. Now that was a other good decision that we have ever made also moving away from all the hustle and bustle, traffic, parking and noise. We just couldn’t keep up or tolerate it anymore. We needed to stretch our legs and have some breathing room. Since we were both in our mid/late 70’s at the time. 🅿️ And we just wanted to slow down in our retirement years and obviously just sitting is not showing any signs of slowing down. It’s just keeps growing growing and growing and getting faster, faster and faster. Going back to the Acura. This car has took us to all the places we always wanted to go /do and see.And we truly did everything we always wanted and talked about doing when we retired. And for the we are truly blessed. Because a lot of people can’t say that. And I am truly thankful to the Acura for that because it had a big impact and role on doing those things. But most of all all the memories that helped us make specially enjoying it with my best friend and all my family for that I am grateful and those are the memories that I hold closest to my heart. It just feels like yesterday, and still puts a smile on my face. Those are the things that are most important things in life I tell you. But now it is time for it to go see a lot more new places and see new things for someone one else. But most of all to make some new memories for its new owner/owners. And I know it will do just that. It still has plenty of life left. It out ran us. It just like the energizer Bunny. It just keeps going going going and going.🐰🐰🐰 Just be good to it and I promise it will be good to you. So please respect our wishes for seeking a new owner/owners that plan on keeping it for has long has you can. And appreciate and take care of it and keep it has original has possible. Just the way have been all of these years. Who knows maybe one day you to can pass it on one day to your next generation to come. Just the way I am doing today. Heck ain’t that what it is all about ??? Passing on good things to the next generation/ generation’s 👍🏻👍🏻👍🏻. I didn’t plan on writing all of these things but I guess the new owner/owners need to know the history of the Acura and how special it has been for us . And played a big part/role in our retirement years in our lives. Well if you have future questions or to schedule an appointment you can call my daughter on her cell phone at  show contact info . ☎️☎️☎️. Please, she had requested that you call her no texting or no emails she will only respond to phone calls. The Acura has a Clean Bill of health, Clean Title, Clean Carfax, New Smog Certificate and Current Registration. We are selling the Acura for $4,950 FIRM… PLEASE SERIOUS CALLERS AND BUYERS ONLY-NO EMAILS NO TEXTING…. THANK YOU FOR INTREST In THE ACURA
